This paper is about optimization algorithms for machine learning applications, which is a common topic in the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper specifically focuses on stochastic optimization, which involves dealing with noisy and incomplete data, making cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) another likely sub-category. The use of variance reduction techniques is also a key aspect of the paper, which is a common topic in cs.NA (Numerical Analysis). Additionally, the paper discusses experiments on real-world datasets for a multiclass classification application, which suggests a possible connection to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CV (Computer Vision).
